<h1>Problem 965 - 2020 Fake USAMO, P3 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(\triangle ABC\) be a scalene triangle with circumcenter \(O\), incenter \(I\), and incircle \(\omega\). Let \(\omega\) touch the sides \(\overline{BC}\), \(\overline{CA}\), and \(\overline{AB}\) at points \(D\), \(E\), and \(F\) respectively. Let \(T\) be the projection of \(D\) to \(\overline{EF}\). The line \(AT\) intersects the circumcircle of \(\triangle ABC\) again at point \(X\ne A\). The circumcircles of \(\triangle AEX\) and \(\triangle AFX\) intersect \(\omega\) again at points \(P\ne E\) and \(Q\ne F\) respectively. Prove that the lines \(EQ\), \(FP\), and \(OI\) are concurrent.</p>
